args:
On the road to Valkaheim, Ciella appears before
Elisanne to warn her that rumors of the prince
being possessed by the Other are spreading.
A messenger then tells the party that citizens
are descending upon the Halidom, so they
change course and head back to New Alberia.

We were spirited back to the Halidom from
the border checkpoint thanks to Zena's power.
And once again, it was beyond my ability to
bring my sister home.
But there's no time for moping.\nWe need to decide what the next step is\nand set our plan in motion right away.
And to do that, we need information—\ninformation on the powers that threaten\nAlberia, and information on my birth.
And so, I decided to head for Valkaheim so I\ncould speak with my brother Leonidas.
Hey, Alex. Do you know where Elly is?
I saw her make for the forest a while ago,\nmostlike for her daily spear training.
Hmm. Valkaheim is still pretty far off;\nI hope she doesn't push herself too hard.
I'm planning on checking on her later,\nbut you know how she is. She has never\nbeen one to cut corners.
Have you talked to her much lately?\nI imagine there's still a lot on her mind.
She seems more centered than she was,\nbut recent events clearly still prey on her.
No doubt she struggles with her own self.
(In all of his magnanimity,\nHis Highness forgave me.)
(But I've not been able to properly\nrespond to His Highness's compassion.)
(Not since the day I was shown\nthat document...)
What is the path I ought to take...?
Ciella! What in the Goddess's name\nare YOU doing here?!
That is a terribly rude attitude to adopt\nfor one who has come all this way.

Silence, witch! What are you plotting!?
If you intend to interfere with His Highness
once more, know that I will cut you down
where you stand!
Surely this is nothing worth getting so\nfurious about? I've merely come here to\nbring you some most vital information.
There is a wicked little rumor about your\nprecious prince creeping across the land.
The word on every lip and tongue is that\nthe seventh scion has been possessed\nby the Other.
Base chicanery! No person of sense would\nbelieve such a thing for a moment!
I do not believe people are nearly the wise\nholders of good sense you think they are.
People do not believe in things because\nthey hew close to the truth—they believe\nin them because it is convenient.

It is no wonder foul rumors swirl in a
kingdom where the royal family's power
has been weakened, thereby plunging the
populace into unease and hard times.

Oh, and one more thing: These rumors
were spread by a group who intend to
take your people down. You'd best
be wary.
As if I would believe a single word\nthat comes from your mouth!
Then whose words DO you believe?
I don't need to throw you off your game;\nyou are currently a mess of indecision\nwithout my even trying to make it so.
Who is it that you believe, Elisanne?\nThe false prince? The deceitful Church?
Fie, this is no time for me to be troubling\nin my mind; I must hurry and inform His\nHighness of what has transpired here.
I did. And though I see no sense in giving\ncredence to her wild claims, I thought it\nbest to inform you regardless.
My darling is NOT possessed by the Other!\nSo rude!
I love a good rumor as much as anyone,\nbut that's just too nutty to be true.
Still, where's a yarn like that start\nspinnin' from in the first place?

The communcation's intent is unclear.
I judge this information of low credibility.
▷Plus, why would someone from Agito
even do something like that?◁
Yeah, Ciella preeeetty much seems to\nhate our guts, but now she wants to be\nall buddy-buddy with the dirty deets?

I know not her angle in this matter,
but based on what I saw of her at the
border, she hates deceit and perfidy far
more fiercely than she does us.
Supposing for a moment that the rumors\nare real, and there is in fact a plot behind\nthem, she might well inform us of it.
Yes, there may very well be something\ngoing on.
Right, we can't ignore this. Let's stop by\nthe next town we find and put our ears\nto the ground to see if rumors are afoot.
We'll set out a bit earlier so we can have\ntime to gather information, so rest up.
Okay, everyone, let's get moving.\nWe've got another full day ahead of—
Hey, ain't that one of the Halidom guards?
*pant* *pant* *pant* Your Highness!\nI've finally caught up with you!
Easy, solider. Ya look like fresh hell.\nSlow down and tell us what's wrong.
After you left, people began to gather, and\nnow surround the castle in such numbers\nwe've no idea how to deal with them.
From where do these troops hail?\nAre they remnants of Dyrenell?
It's not a proper army, but rather citizens\nmassing from all across the land.
This isn't making much sense to me,\nbut we clearly need to deal with it.
Everyone, we're going to put a pause on\nValkaheim and return to the Halidom.
